cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about developing Neural Machine Translation (NMT) models for the Amharic-Arabic language pair. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also uses deep learning techniques such as LSTM and GRU, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the paper involves optimizing the NMT models, which falls under the category of neural engineering (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the models using a BLEU score, which is a common metric used in information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
